{
  "id": "ex_casual_eace2dea",
  "intent": "Run a plant DNA extraction protocol using magnetic beads. Start by lysing samples with a few different buffers while heating to 65\u00b0C, then add precipitation solution and beads to capture the DNA. Do a couple wash steps to clean everything up, then elute the purified DNA at 70\u00b0C. The robot handles all the transfers and uses the magnetic module to separate the beads throughout the process.",
